## 1.2 Deployment Options Extracted

Based on the README, I identified the following deployment options:

| Deployment Option | Status | Description |
|------------------|--------|-------------|
| **Free-installation deployment** | ❌ Not Available | No `npx`, `uvx`, or similar one-command deployment mentioned |
| **Local deployment** | ✅ Available | Clone repo, install dependencies with `pip`, run `python server.py` |
| **Remote deployment** | ❌ Not Available | No cloud-hosted version or remote endpoints provided by developers |
| **Locally installed but transport via remote protocol** | ✅ Available | Server uses HTTP transport (`mcp.run(transport="http", port=8000)`) |

**Note**: The local deployment and "locally installed but transport via remote protocol" are essentially the same in this case - you install locally and the server communicates via HTTP instead of stdio.

